article.description: — Bryce Hamilton had a career-high 45 points as UNLV beat Colorado State 88-74 on Friday night.
article.headline: Hamilton scores 45 to lead UNLV past Colorado St. 88-74
article.linkText: Hamilton scores 45 to lead UNLV past Colorado St. 88-74
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- — Bryce Hamilton had a career-high 45 points as UNLV beat Colorado State 88-74 on Friday night. David Muoka had 11 points for UNLV (12-9, 4-4 Mountain West Conference). Michael Nuga added six rebounds. Isaiah Stevens scored a career-high 35 points and had eight rebounds for the Rams (16-2, 6-2), whose five-game winning streak was broken. David Roddy added 13 points and eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
